      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u help me with my law homework? i'm trying to understand the main arguments that people use to support originalism in constitutional law. what are the key points for it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism in constitutional law is a way of interpreting the Constitution that insists on sticking to the original meaning of the text as understood at the time it was written. Proponents argue that this approach preserves the rule of law and prevents judges from imposing their personal beliefs on the Constitution. It also respects the intentions of the Founding Fathers and maintains a stable legal framework. Originalists believe that any changes to the Constitution should come through the formal amendment process, not through judicial interpretation. This method is seen as a safeguard against judicial activism and ensures that the Constitution remains a living document, adaptable to modern society through the amendment process.",
